    management: ["Administer oxygen to target SpO2 as ordered (88-92% for COPD, > 94% for most others)", "Position in high-Fowler's or tripod position for breathing ease", "Administer bronchodilators and corticosteroids as prescribed", "Implement lung-protective ventilation for ARDS (tidal volume 6-8 mL/kg IBW)", "Maintain PEEP as ordered to recruit alveoli", "Prepare for chest tube insertion for pneumothorax as directed", "Initiate anticoagulation for PE as prescribed", "Implement aspiration precautions for at-risk patients", "Suction airway as needed using sterile technique", "Encourage incentive spirometry and early ambulation post-operatively"],
